Write the setVKnotVector method in the NurbsSurface class.
Remember to respond with a snippet in the form of the following:
```
class NurbsSurface {
    setVKnotVector(vKnotVector) {
        // your code here
    }
}
```

Here is the implementation of the `setVKnotVector` method in the `NurbsSurface` class:

```javascript
class NurbsSurface {
    constructor() {
        this._vKnotVector = [];
        this._vWeights = [];
    }

    setUKnotVector(uKnotVector) {
        // Implementation of setting U knot vector
    }

    setVKnotVector(vKnotVector) {
        if (!Array.isArray(vKnotVector) || vKnotVector.length === 0) {
            throw new Error("Invalid knot vector. It must be a non-empty array.");
        }

        this._vKnotVector = vKnotVector;
    }

    // Additional methods and properties
}
```

This method takes an array `vKnotVector` as input and assigns it to the private `_vKnotVector` property. It also includes a validation check to ensure that the input is a non-empty array, throwing an error otherwise.
